Problem Statment 1

 “Recruiting should be viewed as a business partner,
  someone who is critical to the success of the business.” 

                                                                                    Mathew Caldwell                                                         

In today’s scarce labor market, it is becoming unthinkable for companies to hire professionals they want on their own. It is rather becoming more imperative to choose to pay headhunters to find the best talent. According to the Society for Human Resource Management's (SHRM’s) average cost-per-hire in 2016 was $4,129, while the average time it takes to fill a given position is 42 days.

This is a good article about Society for Human Resource Management

https://www.thebalancecareers.com/society-for-human-resource-management-shrm-1918261
